GeneralHelp
       GENERAL HELP FOR GENMOT PROGRAM            01
                                                  02
The GENMOT program allows you to investigate the  03
dynamics of any system with up to three degrees of04
freedom.                                          05
The differential equations describing the system  06
must be entered as a Pascal Procedure using the   07
examples included with the software as a guide.   08
Once the program has been compiled, the program   09
allows you to investigate the dynamics graphically10
and numerically.                                  11
                                                  12
Important Terms:                                  13
             Dynamical Variables                  14
The time-dependent variables representing the     15
degrees of freedom of the problem (i.e. x(t),     16
v(t), a(t)).                                      17
             Force Parameters                     18
User-modifiable constants that describe the force 19
(i.e. g=9.8 m/s^2)                                20
             User-Defined Functions               21
Functions of the dynamical variables and the      22
force parameters (i.e. EK=1/2 m v^2)              23
                                                  24
Context-sensitive help is obtained by typing F1   25

